<br>
However, in the last year the players have changed dramatically. Now when I play (and yes, I've tried 9 different servers), I find that they treat the game as nothing more than a race to be uber. Consequently, they exclude non-twinks from their groups and guilds. When they get bored, they start an alternate character, twink it to the gills, and move through the low-mid level zones taking every spawn they can get their hands on - with no interest in sharing or following the Rules of Conduct (yes, this is a violation of the rules). I don't know about you, but I'm sick of this behavior, and I know it will only get worse.<br>
<br>
As for replayability, this argument is total bullshit. Anyone at any time can make any character, and enjoy it - without twinking; that is the purpose of the game. There is absolutely no valid reason for giving level 50 gear to a level 1 character. The lack of challenge alone should be so boring that nobody would do it. If you find the game boring, and can't bear to work up another character, then you should cancel your account and go elsewhere - good riddance. Don't take your entertainment at my expense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=phungkuu>Phung Kuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/26/02 11:26:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1636.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Inflammatory?<br>
